			<description><![CDATA[<p>
* Are you a quick study that tends to get bored after three to six months on the same project?<br />
* Like the startup atmosphere, but think it would be nice to learn from more than just a handful of engineers?<br />
* Do you find yourself working on side projects as a way to learn new technologies?<br />
* Wish you could get exposed to a variety of businesses across different industries?<br />
*Do you want to have a real impact solving big problems for some of the best known brands in the world? And also have the opportunity to help build products for cutting-edge startups?</p>
<p>
If any of the above is true then you should consider working at Intridea. Working at Intridea means:</p>
<p>
* Working on an exciting new project every three to six months.<br />
* Working for some of the worlds best known brands solving real business problems.<br />
* Helping startups build and launch products.<br />
* Having the support of 50+ world class designers, engineers, and leaders to make you look good and help you grow.<br />
* Constantly learning new technologies and keeping your skills sharp.<br />
* Never being bored.</p>
<p>
A year at Intridea is equivalent of 5 years at other startups. In a year at Intridea you&#39;ll build two to three products and applications from beginning to end. You&#39;ll learn multiple sets of technologies and you&#39;ll work with several amazing teams. That&#39;s in just one year. Are you ready for the challenge?</p>
<p>
Many of our alumni have gone on to start their own companies, work at organizations like Twitter and Github, or become CTO&#39;s and CIO&#39;s of other startups. How do you want to spend the next few years of your life? Becoming an expert in a narrow set of technologies toiling away at a single application? Or grow like you&#39;ve never done before?</p>
<p>
We&#39;re currently looking for top notch Ruby developers in DC. Backbone.js or other Javascript framework experience is a plus.</p>
